items.title: Delayed September report shows U.S. added 119,000 jobs, more than expected; unemployment rate at 4.4%
items.description: Nonfarm payrolls were expected to add 50,000 in September, according to the Dow Jones consensus estimate.

items.title: The September jobs report is finally coming out Thursday. Here's what it is expected to show
items.description: Due at 8:30 a.m. ET, the report is forecast to show a gain of 50,000 jobs in the public and private sectors.

items.title: Fed minutes show divide over October rate cut and cast doubt about December
items.description: While the Federal Open Market Committee approved a cut at the meeting, the path forward looks less creation.

items.title: BLS says full October jobs data won't be released, available figures to be included in next report
items.description: The Bureau of Labor Statistics said Wednesday it will not release a full U.S. jobs report for the month of October.

items.title: From $1 trillion spending to F-35s, U.S.-Saudi pledges aren't done deals yet
items.description: The leaders signed a defense cooperation pact and held discussions about the sale of American F-35 fighter jets to the kingdom.
